Note that ape, drisk, cyear, sbcountrt are strongly correalated with other variables.

Convert some of the variables into factors and simplify them.

dat$recom[dat$recom != 6] <-1
dat$recom[dat$recom == 6] <-0
dat$recom<-factor(dat$recom,levels=0:1,labels=c("Stay", "Release"))

dat$age = dat$tyear - dat$byear

dat$tage = dat$tyear - dat$byear
dat$tage <-cut(dat$tage, breaks=c(0,18,59,89))
dat$tage <- factor(as.numeric(dat$tage), levels=1:3, labels=c("Children", "Adults", "Seniors"))

dat$detlength = dat$ryear- dat$tyear+1

dat$health[dat$health==1] = 0
dat$health[dat$health>1] = 1
dat$health<-factor(dat$health,levels=c(0,1),labels=c("Bad health", "Not bad health"))

dat$saffiliation[dat$saffiliation==3]<-1
dat$saffiliation[dat$saffiliation==4]<-3
dat$saffiliation[dat$saffiliation==5]<-0
dat$saffiliation <-factor(dat$saffiliation,levels=0:3,labels=c("No Affiliation", "AQ", "TB", "Other"))

dat$intel[dat$intel==3]<-2
dat$intel[dat$intel==4]<-3
dat$intel[dat$intel==7]<-0
dat$intel<-factor(dat$intel, levels=0:3,labels=c("No Intel", "Low", "Medium", "High"))

dat$ublbg = factor(dat$ublbg, levels = 0:2, labels = c("Low", "Medium", "High"))

dat$risk = factor(dat$risk, levels = 0:3, labels = c("No", "Low", "Medium", "High"))
dat$drisk = factor(dat$drisk, levels = 0:3, labels = c("No", "Low", "Medium", "High"))

dat$ecstat[dat$ecstat ==9] <- 2
dat$ecstat = factor(dat$ecstat, levels = 0:2, labels = c("No", "Yes", "Not clear"))

dat$rft[dat$rft==8] <- 3
dat$rft[dat$rft==9] <- 4
dat$rft = factor(dat$rft, levels = 0:4, labels = c("No Recorded Reason", "To Provide Information", "Prosecution", "Affiliation With TB/AQ", "Membership in AQ"))

colnames(dat)[14] = 'hungerstrike'
dat$hungerstrike[dat$hungerstrike > 0] <- 1
dat$hungerstrike = factor(dat$hungerstrike, levels = 0:1, labels = c("No","Yes"))

dat$snat = factor(dat$snat)
dat$sbcountry = factor(dat$sbcountry)
dat$sccountry = factor(dat$sccountry)

levels(dat$snat) = c("Afghanistan","Algeria","Aserbaijan","Australia","Bahrain","Belgium","Bangladesh","Bosnia & Herzigovina","Canada","Chad","China","Denmark","Egypt","Ethiopia","France","Great Britain","Indonesia","Iran","Italy","Iraq","Jordan","Kenya","Kuwait","Kazachstan","Libya","Morocco","Mauritania","Maldives","Malaysia","Niger","Palestine","Pakistan","Qatar","Russia","Saudi Arabia","Somalia","Spain","Sudan","Sweden","Syria","Tajikistan","Tunisia","Turkey","Turkmenistan","Tanzania","United Arab Emirates","Uganda","Uzbekistan","Yemen","Zambia")

We decide to remove rdi and assault since they have over 60% data missing. We also decided to remove some variables with high correlations with other variables. We have removed: ape, drisk, cyear and sbcountry. We also removed random since it is meaningless

dat$random = NULL
dat$rdi = NULL
dat$assault = NULL
dat$ape = NULL
dat$drisk = NULL
dat$cyear = NULL
dat$sbcountry = NULL

For some of the variables, we decide to do some imputations with the missing values.

dat$ecstat[is.na(dat$ecstat)==TRUE] <- "Not clear"

dat$preape[is.na(dat$preape)==TRUE] <- 0

dat$hungerstrike[is.na(dat$hungerstrike)==TRUE]<- "No"

dat$rft[is.na(dat$rft)==TRUE] <- "No Recorded Reason"

dat$ublbg[is.na(dat$ublbg)==TRUE] <- "Low"

dat$health[is.na(dat$health)==TRUE]<-"Not bad health"

dat$saffiliation[is.na(dat$saffiliation)==TRUE]<- "No Affiliation"

dat$risk[is.na(dat$risk)==TRUE] <- "No"

dat$recom[is.na(dat$recom)==TRUE] <- "Stay"

dat$intel[is.na(dat$intel)==TRUE] <- "No Intel"

Fitting the model

We use collab as our response and will not include outdeg in our model. Also, since tage is a combination of tyear and byear, we will not include tyear and byear in the model. ryear is not included for the same reason since we have detlength.

fullmod = glm(collab ~ snat+health+recom+risk+intel+ecstat+hungerstrike+sccountry+preape+saffiliation+ublbg+rft+age+indeg+detlength,data = newdat, family = binomial)

Predict whether an inmate will collaborate or not using the model without interaction terms

prediction = predict(stepmod, newdat)

for (i in 1:nrow(newdat))
{
  if (prediction[i] >= 1)
  {
    prediction[i] = 1
  } 
  else
  {
    prediction[i] = 0
  }
}
prediction = factor(prediction, levels = 0:1, labels = c("Non collaboration", "Collaboration"))

Compare this prediction to actual data

count = 0
for (i in 1:nrow(newdat)){
  if (prediction[i] == newdat$collab[i]){
    count = count + 1
  }
}
count
## [1] 452

Correctly predicted 452 inmates collaboration out of 684 cases

Predict whether an inmate will collaborate or not using the model with interaction terms

prediction = predict(stepmod.add.interactionmod.step, newdat)

for (i in 1:nrow(newdat))
{
  if (prediction[i] >= 1)
  {
    prediction[i] = 1
  } 
  else
  {
    prediction[i] = 0
  }
}
prediction = factor(prediction, levels = 0:1, labels = c("Non collaboration", "Collaboration"))
count = 0
for (i in 1:nrow(newdat)){
  if (prediction[i] == newdat$collab[i]){
    count = count + 1
  }
}

We will use the simplest model to explain the relationship of collab with other variables.

Plot the model coefficients

par(mar=c(5,12,4,2))
CI.lower<-summary(stepmod)$coefficients[,1]-1.96*summary(stepmod)$coefficients[,2]
CI.upper<-summary(stepmod)$coefficients[,1]+1.96*summary(stepmod)$coefficients[,2]
CI<-cbind(CI.lower,CI.upper)[-1,]
matplot(CI, cbind(1:dim(CI)[1],1:dim(CI)[1]),pch=1,col=1,lty=2,ylab="",xlab="coefficient",axes=F)
abline(v=0)
segments(x0=CI[,1], y0=1:dim(CI)[1],x1=CI[,2], y1=1:dim(CI)[1],lty=2)
axis(1)
par(las=2)
axis(2,at=1:dim(CI)[1],labels=rownames(CI),tick=F)
title(main = "Coefficient Values")
